Two Chinese nationals working with a glass and aluminium company in Benin, the Edo State capital, have been abducted by gunmen. It was gathered that a  police personnel  attached to them was killed during the kidnap operation. It was further gathered that the victims were abducted on Wednesday evening at Utesi community (a suburb of Benin) on the Benin-Auchi road, where their company is located. OVER 5,000 NIGERIAN MEN HAVE  OVERCOME POOR BEDROOM PERFORMANCE SYNDROME DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY. CLICK HERE TO KNOW MORE The victims were said to be on their way home when the gunmen blocked their vehicle and abducted them after killing the police officer attached to them. A source who spoke with our reporter in confidence, said, “As soon as the victims came out of the company, the gunmen who apparently have been waiting for them, started trailing them.” The source said the gunmen killed the security officer attached to the victims while shooting sporadically before abducting the victims. When contacted, the Edo State Commissioner of Police, DanMallam Muhammed, confirmed the incident. He said, “Yes, the incident was reported to us yesterday (Wednesday). We are working hard to rescue them from the kidnappers.” He also confirmed that the police personnel attached to the victims was killed during the process of abduction. The commissioner assured that the perpetrators would be apprehended and brought to justice. Edo: Gunmen abduct Chinese nationals, kill police officer Gunmen abduct police officer, four others in Edo Police rescue seven as one dies during abduction in Edo Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin